{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596082","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596082"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15391"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15391","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15391"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.26,0,0.74,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8082"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63588"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8082","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8082"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15391"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49042"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19613"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19615"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20856"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63588"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EUlcerative colitis is a form of chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In planning treatment it is important to consider risk factors that could influence the severity of the disease.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is associated with a more severe disease course?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Late onset of symptoms","High serum albumin","Limited disease extent","Young age at diagnosis","Normal C-reactive protein"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESeveral factors are associated with a more severe disease course in ulcerative colitis:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EYoung age at diagnosis\u003C/strong\u003E (particularly before age 40) is associated with more extensive disease and increased risk of colectomy\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh serum albumin\u003C/strong\u003E is actually protective - low albumin indicates severe disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELimited disease extent\u003C/strong\u003E typically indicates a better prognosis - extensive colitis carries worse outcomes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELate onset of symptoms\u003C/strong\u003E generally indicates milder disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EElevated, not \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal C-reactive protein\u003C/strong\u003E, predicts more severe disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther poor prognostic factors include deep ulceration on endoscopy, elevated inflammatory markers, and need for early corticosteroids.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Elevated inflammatory markers, young age at diagnosis, extensive disease, and low serum albumin are associated with more severe ulcerative colitis.","Early identification of severity predictors helps guide appropriate treatment decisions in ulcerative colitis."],"references":["McDowell C, Farooq U, Haseeb M. Inflammatory Bowel Disease. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262182","Fakhoury M, Negrulj R, Mooranian A, Al-Salami H. Inflammatory bowel disease: clinical aspects and treatments. J Inflamm Res. 2014 Jun 23;7:113-20. doi: 10.2147/JIR.S65979. PMID: 25075198; PMCID: PMC4106026","Tavakoli P, Vollmer-Conna U, Hadzi-Pavlovic D, Grimm MC. A Review of Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A Model of Microbial, Immune and Neuropsychological Integration. Public Health Rev. 2021 May 5;42:1603990. doi: 10.3389/phrs.2021.1603990. PMID: 34692176; PMCID: PMC8386758","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49042"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15391"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49042"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-21T19:08:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-21T19:08:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8082"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63588"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"da